comments: There are a few issues with this experiment. First, often times I would come up with a label, only to discover that you have a very narrow definition of what that label should be. For the general 'monkey' label, I put 'primates', which should have been an acceptable response, but it wasn't, based on your narrow definitions. I changed the label to what you wanted, but it made me wonder what you could possibly be testing. Also, I feel that some of the images stretch what would be commonly known - is anyone really supposed to know that one of your dog images was a Great Dane? Or that the tree was a Sequoia, not an Oak? Perhaps it would help if the images were photos instead of illustrations, but probably not.
